news.news: Wiggins logged 18 points (7-13 FG, 1-3 3Pt, 3-4 FT), four rebounds and one assist over 26 minutes during Sunday's 129-99 loss to the Kings.
news.analysis: Jonathan Kuminga (ankle) is expected to miss significant time, which may mean more production for Wiggins, who's made strides after a brief slump at the end of the December. Next to Draymond Green, Wiggins is Golden State's best defender, and he was able to curb some of Sacramento's production by harassing DeMar DeRozan throughout the game.
